{"author":{"id":"U_kgDOCGOM3A","is_bot":false,"login":"kapilvirenahuja","name":"Kapil Viren Ahuja"},"baseRefName":"main","body":"## Summary\n\nRecompiles the 13 strategy and lens plays — agentic, arch, grill, learn, marketing,\nmeasure, quality, roadmap, run, shape, understand, ux, vision — onto the Level 3 pattern\nalready piloted in Batch A (end-sequence) and Batch B (execute-pipe). Done means is now\nderived per play from its own existing done bar; C0 stop-condition gates plus session\nidentity stamps were added to all 13; mid-flight checkpoints that were previously\nmandatory become config-gated switches per the approved intent change, defaulted ON,\nbehavior unchanged — with two exceptions the intent explicitly pins: vision's\nbrief-approval checkpoint stays pinned, and grill's human loop stays uncapped\n(mandatory, not switchable).\n\nMeasure's stamp script picked up the dual-outcome stamp record. Quality's apply script\nallowlist now admits `lens/quality-gates.yaml` (the #462 machine sibling) alongside\n`lens/quality.md` — a latent bug fix, since the allowlist would previously have refused\nthe gates file — and its out-manifest now carries `lens_applied` /\n`gates_machine_applied` for the stop-condition gate to read. A handful of other apply/\nstamp scripts (grill's validate_epics, roadmap's compute_plan, and the apply scripts for\nlearn, marketing, shape, ux, vision, agentic) were extended the same way, so each play's\nown stop-condition gate can read machine fields instead of prose.\n\n## Self-Review Checklist\n\nRules resolved from: `/Users/kapilahuja/.garura/core/memory/standards/rules/self-review.md`\n(base, no project override)\n\n### Scope checks\n\n- **Matches the issue.** PASS. All 80 changed files are the 13 recompiled plays plus\n  STM context artifacts for #466. Nothing outside this footprint.\n- **No scope creep.** PASS. No unrelated files touched.\n- **Reasonable size.** PASS with note. 5,219 insertions is large for one sitting, but it\n  is 13 structurally-identical play recompiles (each diff the same shape) plus\n  byte-identical checker/stamp scripts repeated per play.\n- **No stray artifacts.** PASS. No commented-out blocks, debug prints, or scratch files.\n\n### Quality checks\n\n- **Tests present.** PASS (mechanical verification in place of unit tests — this is a\n  play/recipe change). Ran `lint_play.py` against all 24 plays now on the Level 3\n  pattern (5 Batch A + 6 Batch B + 13 Batch C) — all return `VERDICT: PASS (0 gap(s))`.\n- **Checker copies byte-identical.** PASS — verified via `md5` across all 13 plays'\n  `scripts/check_stop_condition.py` and `scripts/session_stamp.py`: single hash each, no\n  differences across any pair.\n- **Commits are clean.** PASS. Conventional format, all reference #466.\n- **No secrets.** PASS. Grepped diff for api-key/secret/password/token patterns — no\n  credential values, only legitimate prose hits.\n- **Docs in step.** PASS. Each play's `reference/ice.md` recompiled alongside its\n  `SKILL.md` in the same commit, per the play pipeline rule.\n- **Nothing obviously broken.** PASS. No TODOs or known-failing paths introduced.\n\n### Verdict\n\n**PASS — 0 FAIL, 0 blocking findings.** 1 non-blocking note (size, explained by\nstructural repetition across 13 plays). Cleared to raise.\n\n## Loop note\n\nThis batch's own commit converged in 3 rounds: two executor re-entry defects were found\nand logged during the build loop, and the verdict held 4/4 before the batch was accepted\nas done.\n\nRefs #466\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)","commits":[{"authoredDate":"2026-07-04T06:23:39Z","authors":[{"email":"kapil@howtoarchitect.io","id":"U_kgDOCGOM3A","login":"kapilvirenahuja","name":"Kapil Viren Ahuja"}],"committedDate":"2026-07-04T06:23:39Z","messageBody":"…ne fields across the 13 strategy and lens plays (#466)","messageHeadline":"feat(components): roll out batch C stop-condition machinery and machi…","oid":"88f5bd3c831f3c0db0fdcc8b7120b